Here are a few websites where you can find basic information about Windows user interface (UI) settings:1. **Microsoft Support** [support.microsoft.com](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us) Official Microsoft documentation that covers all aspects of Windows settings, including user interface settings like themes, taskbar, and display preferences.2. **Windows Central** [www.windowscentral.com](https://www.windowscentral.com) A popular site for Windows tips and tricks, including guides on customizing and tweaking the UI for a more personalized experience.3. **How-To Geek** [www.howtogeek.com](https://www.howtogeek.com) A technology site that frequently publishes articles about optimizing and customizing Windows, including UI and accessibility settings.4. **TenForums** [www.tenforums.com](https://www.tenforums.com) A community-driven website for Windows 10 users, offering guides, tutorials, and discussions on UI customizations.5. **BleepingComputer** [www.bleepingcomputer.com](https://www.bleepingcomputer.com) A tech site with articles and tutorials on Windows, including UI customization, security, and maintenance.These resources should help you explore the various ways to adjust the user interface on your Windows system.
